questions_and_answers.question: Kentucky business scaling
questions_and_answers.answer: Kentucky has no state-wide general contractor licensing requirement. Louisville and Lexington require business licenses for contractors. Specific trades (electrical, plumbing) are regulated at state level. Home improvement contractors must register for projects over $200. Public works requires prequalification through state transportation department.
